-- Ben Affleck Wins Directing Globe for ‘Argo’ After Oscar Snub
-- B y   A n d y   F i x m e r
-- 2013-01-14T03:24:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-14/ben-affleck-wins-directing-globe-for-argo-after-oscar-snub.html
Ben Affleck  won the Golden Globe for
directing “Argo,” after being shut out from the Oscar
nominations in the same category.  Actresses Amy Poehler and Tina Fey hosted the ceremony
tonight from Beverly Hills, California. “Lincoln” leads the
nominations with seven, including best picture and best
director.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andy Fixmer in Los Angeles at 
 afixmer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
